HARTINGSON, Respondent, v. FORTY-SECOND ST. & M. R. CO, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. May 18, 1894.) Action by Max Hartingson against the Forty-Second Street & Manhattanville Railroad Company.

Argued before O’BRIEN, FOLLETT, and PARKER, JJ.

A. Kling, for appellant. J. Fromme, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs.
